      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Missy J" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Missy J" href="/user/show/7406091-missy-j">Missy J</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780802170774" href="/book/show/7029668-purge">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/7406091-missy-j?shelf=2016-books">2016-books</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/7406091-missy-j?shelf=historical-fiction">historical-fiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/7406091-missy-j?shelf=europe-related">europe-related</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1668305786" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer5464461186883915804"><img src='https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/hostedimages/1466234365i/19454991._SX540_.jpg' width='320' height='240' alt='description' class='gr-hostedUserImg'/><br/>Estonian forest.<br/><br/>Wow! What a story! If it weren&apos;t for my book club, I wouldn&apos;t have picked this book up! I tried reading this four years ago, but due to a hectic schedule, gave up. However, four days ago, I picked it up again and was sucked into the story!<br/><br/>Where do I begin? One morning in 1992, Aliide Truu, an elderly woman, who used to be a Communist when Estonia was part of the Soviet Union, finds a bruised young woman in her garden. Now if I were Aliide, I would have rushed outside to help the </span>
  <span id="freeText5464461186883915804" style="display:none"><img src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/hostedimages/1466234365i/19454991._SX540_.jpg" width="320" height="240" alt="description" class="gr-hostedUserImg"><br>Estonian forest.<br><br>Wow! What a story! If it weren't for my book club, I wouldn't have picked this book up! I tried reading this four years ago, but due to a hectic schedule, gave up. However, four days ago, I picked it up again and was sucked into the story!<br><br>Where do I begin? One morning in 1992, Aliide Truu, an elderly woman, who used to be a Communist when Estonia was part of the Soviet Union, finds a bruised young woman in her garden. Now if I were Aliide, I would have rushed outside to help the girl and call help. However, Aliide approaches the situation with a very high level of distrust and believes the girl to be a decoy. <br><br>"Purge" gives the reader a good general overview of Estonia from when the country was occupied by Soviets and Germans during World War II to its relapse to Soviet communist rule for 50 years. The book traces where Aliide Truu's mistrust comes from. I now also understand why Estonia has close ties to Germany and have learned that Estonians are closely related to Finnish people (both Estonian and Finnish are Uralic languages, not Indo-European). <br><br>The author skips a lot between the past and the present, and different narrators are used at random. Themes, which are dealt with intensively in this book include; horrendous prostitution, human trafficking and the Russian mafia, sibling rivalry, obsessive love, betrayal, self-reliance, and how the communist system turned people against each other. There are some truly gruesome scenes in this book, so it's not a light read, but definitely a page-turner! Overall, this book gave me a real taste of this Eastern European country, its Communist past and how the shadow of the past still lingers around in the present.</span>
  <a data-text-id="5464461186883915804" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


