<div id="review_2479914521" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2479914521" />
    <a title="Sadie" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/3057525-sadie"><img alt="Sadie" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1557910132p2/3057525.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2479914521?book_show_action=true">Dec 21, 2018</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Sadie" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Sadie" href="/user/show/3057525-sadie">Sadie</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Kindle Edition " href="/book/show/11163457-purge">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3057525-sadie?shelf=ty-fiction">ty-fiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3057525-sadie?shelf=g-novel">g-novel</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3057525-sadie?shelf=read-author-female-only">read-author-female-only</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3057525-sadie?shelf=read-in-2018">read-in-2018</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3057525-sadie?shelf=read-in-english">read-in-english</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3057525-sadie?shelf=z-multigenerational">z-multigenerational</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3057525-sadie?shelf=z-shifting-povs">z-shifting-povs</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3057525-sadie?shelf=medium-kindle">medium-kindle</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3057525-sadie?shelf=4-stars-really-liked">4-stars-really-liked</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3057525-sadie?shelf=x-made-me-fret">x-made-me-fret</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2479914521" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer1116033045131470275">A dark story full of violence, betrayal, guilt and horror, set in a rather depressing place and time, written in a bleak way - no, this isn&apos;t any kind of happy-go-lucky-story. However, reading this was most satisfying, since as a dark novel, as a work of literary fiction that makes one fret, it delivers on all accounts.<br/><br/>It&apos;s a story of two women, seperated by many years and lots of history, united in their fate largely shaped by men (and their own reactions towards what these men do - or didn&apos;t d</span>
  <span id="freeText1116033045131470275" style="display:none">A dark story full of violence, betrayal, guilt and horror, set in a rather depressing place and time, written in a bleak way - no, this isn't any kind of happy-go-lucky-story. However, reading this was most satisfying, since as a dark novel, as a work of literary fiction that makes one fret, it delivers on all accounts.<br /><br />It's a story of two women, seperated by many years and lots of history, united in their fate largely shaped by men (and their own reactions towards what these men do - or didn't do). Aliide is the older of the two and more like the main character. Her actions determine pretty much the whole outcome of the novel. She isn't a really sympathetic character, despite the things she has to go through and that hardened her. We get to know her fate step by step, the novel switches back and forth in time and gradually peels away the layers of unrequited love, political opression, the decline of a family and lots and lots of violence. <br /><br />The younger woman, Zara, is, in some way, the result of those years of love/hate, betrayal and deceipt - at the same time, her own fate was shaped in a similarly violent way. Both women, each in their own respective way, did everything they could for their dream to come true - only to find their dream not just shattered, but exploding right in front of their face. <br /><br />Make no mistake, this is a tough read, and even though it's spiced with a pinch of redemption every now and then, the impact of "OMG, how could you" keeps the upper hand. And it all fits, the darkness, the bleak tone, the - for me - rather exotic setting of (politically) surpressed Estonia. For this is not only a story about two women, but also about a country, a time &amp; place, about the Estonian people trying to find their way.<br /><br />Spoiler for the ending - don't peak if you consider reading this at some point, it's for your own good, trust me... <a class="jsShowSpoiler spoilerAction">(view spoiler)</a><span class="spoilerContainer" style="display: none">[Kudos to Sofi Oksanen for the final twist revealed in the "Top Secret Files". Just as I was getting ready to grant Aliide <i>some</i> idea of redemption - even after what she did to Hans, in the end, she kind of "came full circle" by killing Zara's pimps - the secret files revealed her spying and ultimate very own responsibility for her sister's deportation, and I really didn't see that coming. What a blow, what a final shocking twist. <a class="jsHideSpoiler spoilerAction">(hide spoiler)</a>]</span><br /><br />Absolutely recommended for those who like their reading material to take them one step further into the dark unknown.</span>
  <a data-text-id="1116033045131470275" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


